By August 15 of each odd-numbered year, the Office of State Budget Director, in conjunction with the consensus forecasting group, shall provide to each branch of government a budget planning report. The budget planning report shall include:
A baseline analysis and projections of economic conditions and outlook;
Any potential consequences of the analysis and projections for the Commonwealth's fiscal condition;
The revenue estimates and implications for the general fund and road fund for the current fiscal year and next four (4) fiscal years; and
Projections of personal income, employment, and economic indicators that reflect economic conditions.
